text: Solène Jambaqué (born April 14, 1988) is a skier from France. She has a disability. She skied at the 2011 IPC Alpine Skiing World Championships. She was the third skier to finish in the standing women's downhill race and was the first skier to finish in the Super G race and Super Combined race. ==References== Category:French skiers Category:Living people Category:1988 births Category:French sportspeople with disabilities Category:Sportspeople from Toulouse
